</aside
  ><p>That number explains why earlier this summer, Pence decided he could finally live with some federal intrusion; Indiana is now chasing those pre-K funds. (<em>As governor, I fought for Indiana&#8217;s neediest children...</em>)</p><p>But it also explains why Pence seems so eager to accept the VP slot, should Trump offer it. Surely&nbsp;there&#8217;s a better future for vice presidential nominees, even losing ones, than there is for defeated incumbent governors.</p><p>As a connoisseur of power, Trump&nbsp;must understand Pence&#8217;s motives. But he also must know&nbsp;that those motives make Pence an ideal partner: He&#8217;ll do what he&#8217;s told, even if it contradicts his actual beliefs, just so long as it&#8217;s good for the career of Mike Pence.</p><p><em>Craig Fehrman is working on a book about presidents and their writings. He <a href="http://www.indianapolismonthly.com/news-opinion/incoming-mike-pence/" target="_blank">profiled Pence for Indianapolis Monthly</a> in 2013.&nbsp;</em></p><p><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong><strong>Follow the Opinion section on Twitter&nbsp;<a href="https://twitter.com/latimesopinion">@latimesopinion</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/latimesopinion">Facebook</a></strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></strong></p><p><strong>ALSO</strong></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-0515-mcmanus-election-forecasts-20160515-column.html">Election forecasting in the age of Trump</a></strong></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-bustillos-dimon-clinton-sanders-20160713-snap-story.html#nt=oft03a-1la1">The Democrats just ceded economic justice to Donald Trump</a></strong></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.latimes.com/opinion/op-ed/la-oe-ghostbusters-20160713-snap-htmlstory.html#nt=oft03a-1gp3">America could be 4 months away from electing its first female president. So why can't we handle an all-women 'Ghostbusters'?</a></strong></p><div class="trb_eg trb_eg_b" data-role="base_eg delayload base_expandable" data-load-event="base_loadjointeg" data-eg-type="embedRelated"></div></div>
